description.narrative:
More specifically, the project aims to:
- Documentation of institutional violence and abuse of law enforcement agencies in order to produce knowledge about their actors, the extent of their use, the places where they are practiced, their perceptions and their impact on young people (research) ;
- the promotion of a participatory approach to the involvement of young people from the interior and working-class areas in the fight against police abuse and torture (dialogue);
- Sensitization of public authorities (security, civilians at local and national level), media (alternative, social, national) and elected bodies (parliament ...) to human rights and the need to combat impunity in these regions (advocacy);
- Support and reinforcement of local associations in the fight against police violence and the promotion of the rule of law in favor of young people from the working class (trainings, campaigns);
- The development of forms of accompaniment for young victims of police violence and abuse in collaboration with local authorities and associations (assistance).
